knowledge_graph.title: White-collar worker
knowledge_graph.description: A white-collar worker is a person who performs professional, managerial, or administrative work. White-collar work may be performed in an office or other administrative setting.

related_questions.question: What do you mean by white collar job?
related_questions.snippet: Refers to employees whose job entails, largely or entirely, mental or clerical work, such as in an office. The term white collar work used to characterize non-manual workers, but now it refers to employees or professionals whose work is knowledge intensive, non-routine, and unstructured.
